证据片段: The stress-induced orientation of dislocation loops makes a negligible contribution to irradiation creep of zirconium alloys at all stresses.

文献ID: STP633-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_3rd Volume_030_chunk4
证据片段: At the lower stresses $( < 1 5 0 \ \mathrm { M P a } )$ , the stress-induced preferred absorption of irradiation-produced interstitials and vacancies to suitably oriented dislocations is a possible mechanism for in-reactor creep of cold-worked materials but not for annealed materials in which the dislocation density is too low for recombination of point defects to be negligible.
